 2 Related Work CPU-based verification,"A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
"The academic record for exhaustive Goldbach verification is 4 × 1018 [3], achieved through highly cache-efficient segmented sieves with bitwise bulk-marking, targeting O(Nlog logN ) complexity with small constants","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
 Earlier milestones include Richstein’s verification to 4 × 1014 [5],"A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
" These CPU approaches benefit from decades of cache-hierarchy tuning and are extremely competitive at moderate scales; however, they require large distributed clusters to push the frontier meaningfully beyond 10 15","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
