1 Architectural progression The two GoldbachGPU papers represent a sequential elimination of bottlenecks,"A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
" The first [ 4] demonstrated that VRAM exhaustion was an architectural artefact of monolithic prime-table storage, solvable by segmentation at O(1) VRAM cost (14 MB at default parameters)","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
" That work then exposed a second bottleneck: the host CPU, which had to regenerate and transfer each segment bitset","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
 The present architecture resolves this by making the GPU entirely self-sufficient for sieve generation,"A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
" The result is true O(1) host-device communication per segment: rather than transferring the entire segment bitset, the host only uploads the constant array of candidate primes ( ≈ 628 KB at PSMALL = 106) and downloads a 4-byte reduction integer, remaining strictly independent of the segment size","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
