"Conjunctive composi- tion:All subconditions refer to thesametarget, forming an “and”-style conjunction",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" To ensure every subcondition matters, we verify that no proper subset uniquely determines the answer: each condition only removes part of the candidate set, and only the full conjunction yields a single solution",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 This prevents shortcuts where the model can ignore part of the query,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" Sequential composition:Subconditions must be resolvedin order, where later subconditions depend on intermediate entities or states established earlier",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" For example, a first subcondition identifies an object, the second constrains its behavior at a later time, and a third asks about a relation involving that same object after another event",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" The model must carry the referent forward across steps, inducing a multi-hop perceptual reasoning process in which early errors propagate",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 6,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
3,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
"4 Answer Space Each question is formed by composing subconditions, and the final answer is a piece of perceptual information extracted from the video",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 Answers fall into six categories: •Objects: Category names (e,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
g,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
", “car”, “sofa”)",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" •Attributes: Properties such as color, count, or shape",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 •Relationships: Semantic/spatial/social relations between entities,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 •Location: Place descriptors (e,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
g,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
", room type, country, or region)",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 •Action: The name of an action performed by an agent,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 •Event: A higher-level event or composite situation that occurs in the video,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 We cast every question as a five-way multiple-choice problem,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" To discourage reliance on language priors, all distractors are drawn from thesameanswer category as the correct option (e",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
g,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
", all colors or all object categories)",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" Each option is constrained to a single word or a very short phrase, minimizing extra linguistic cues",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 3,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
"5 Difficulty Annotation To enable difficulty-aware evaluation, we ask expert annotators to assign each question to one of three difficulty levels (Level 1/2/3) based on both (i) the number of composed subconditions and (ii) the intrinsic difficulty of the subconditions",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 This avoids treating difficulty as a function of subcondition count alone,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 As shown in Fig,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" 2(b), higher difficulty levels typically contain more subconditions, reflecting increased compositional depth and stronger requirements for long-horizon, perception-centric reasoning",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 3,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
"6 Annotation Pipeline Following the procedure above, we select 279 videos with high scene complexity and annotate 1,114 questions",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" Because each question is highly compositional, we adopt fully manual annotation to ensure correctness",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 Representative annotated examples are shown in Fig,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 3,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" Annotators first create the subconditions and final answer, then verify that (i) the answer is uniquely determined by the video and (ii) every subcondition is necessary",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 Each question is subsequently checked by at least one additional annotator who did not create it,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" During verification, we confirm again that there is a single correct answer and that no proper subset of subconditions suffices to uniquely identify it",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 Items that fail either requirement are revised or discarded,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 This protocol ensures each question admits a unique solution and genuinely requires the full set of composed perceptual subconditions,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 4 Experiments This section evaluates state-of-the-art multimodal LLMs (MLLMs) on PerceptionComp to quantify its difficulty and diagnose current model limitations,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 We first report comprehensive benchmark results across a broad set of open-source and proprietary models (section 4,PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
1),PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
 We then analyze how perception and reasoning budgets affect performance by varying the number of input frames and the allocated thinking-token budget (section B),PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" Finally, we present qualitative case studies and error patterns to highlight common failure modes in perception-centric long-horizon video reasoning (section 4",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
4),PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
" Throughout, our goal is not only to rank models, but also to identify which aspects of perception-centric long-horizon reasoning remain brittle under clutter, scene changes, and compositional constraints",PerceptionComp: A Video Benchmark for Complex Perception-Centric Reasoning
