1 Overview The ChatGE framework introduces a new paradigm of game development as Human-LLM interaction,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" In user-LLM interactions, the user provides instruc- tions for their game concept in natural language under the guidance of LLM, along with feedback to the LLM",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" The LLM guides the user in refin- ing and clarifying essential details about the game, while also offering feedback",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" To enable the LLM to provide effective guidance, we predefine a generic script template tailored to a specific type of game",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Except for interaction with the user, the LLM gen- erates script segments and code snippets to imple- ment the user’s game concept in each turn",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Mean- while, the code snippets are stored, building toward the eventual complete game code, CustomGame",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" After the game is fully developed through multi- turn interactions, a code interpreter is used to exe- cute the CustomGame code for play",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
