" 4 Data Generation In this section, we discuss our attempt in data gen- eration",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 Utilizing LLMs to create ChatGE requires fine-tuning on a substantial amount of supervised data,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" However, manually crafting diverse interac- tions with script-code pairs is a challenging task",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Compared to fully manual annotation, harnessing LLMs to synthesize data is more efficient and has become a popular method for addressing the issue of insufficient data",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" We propose a pipeline consist- ing of three main steps to synthesize data, starting with a small set of manually annotated seed data, as illustrated in Figure 3",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 We utilize GPT-4o as the generator,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Init pool First, we manually craft a few script- code pairs, each corresponding to different custom games",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" These pairs serve as seed data and are then split into script segments and code snippets, which are added to the pool",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Generate new pairs In this step, we sample pairs of script segments and code snippets, generating new pairs based on these selections",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" We prompt the generator to modify the code snippet first, then generate the corresponding script segment",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" This order is chosen because it’s easier to map a script segment to a code snippet by describing the code, rather than generating code from a script descrip- tion",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 This approach yields higher-quality data with more reliable mappings,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" To ensure the generated code functions correctly, we implement a filter to discard code that fails to execute",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 This process con- tinues until the pool contains a sufficient number of entries,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Generate interaction data Finally, we generate the interaction data depicted in Figure 1 using the script-code pairs",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 This process involves two lines: (1) generating interaction snippets based on pairs of script segments and code snippets from the pool; (2) generating complete interactions from complete script-code pairs,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 The necessity of these two data components will be discussed in the next section,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" 5 Training Strategy In this section, we present our training strategy",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" In our framework, the LLM will perform Pscript, Pcode and Putter step by step, which challenges the joint capability of interaction and programming",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" On the other hand, a straightforward strategy to",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
train on sufficient complete interaction data is in- efficient,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Therefore, we propose a three-stage pro- gressive training strategy to transfer the dialogue- based LLM to our ChatGE smoothly",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 Stage-1: Base Training This stage aims to train the base interaction ability of the model,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 Inter- action ability is the most fundamental ability for ChatGE and serves as the foundation for the fol- lowing two stages,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 Since most LLMs have already undergone sufficient and efficient supervised fine- tuning (SFT) (Brown et al,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
", 2020; Raffel et al",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
", 2020; Ouyang et al",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
", 2022), we can directly use such models for Stage-1",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Stage-2: Core Training This stage aims to train the core capabilities of the model, namely the joint capability of programming and interaction",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 It fine- tunes the model from Stage-1 on interaction snip- pets that follow the ChatGE format,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" As illustrated in Figure 1, we instruct the model to perform the Pscript, Pcode and Putter step by step to extract the user’s concept of the game, implement it in code, and provide guidance and feedback for interaction",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 Stage-3: Alignment This stage aims to align the model with a complete interaction context to fully develop a game as a ChatGE,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" It fine-tunes the model from Stage-2, which already possesses sig- nificant programming and interaction capabilities",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" At this stage, we only need to extend its ability for multi-turn interactions as a ChatGE, particularly in guiding users to complete game development according to the predefined script",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Since the model already possesses strong multi-turn interaction and long-context capabilities following Stage-1 train- ing, only a small dataset is required for alignment at this stage",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
