"While I was planning these lectures I happened to reread Ken W ilson’s account of his early work[1], and was struck by the parallel between string theory today and quantum ﬁeld theory thirty years ago",string theory
" Then, as now, one had a good tech nical control over the perturbation theory but little else",string theory
" Wilson saw himself as a sking the question “What is quantum ﬁeld theory?” I found it enjoyable and inspiring to r ead about the various models he studied and approximations he tried (he refers to “clutch ing at straws”) before he found the simple and powerful answer, that the theory is to be organ ized scale-by-scale rather than graph-by-graph",string theory
" That understanding made it possible to ans wer both problems of principle, such as how quantum ﬁeld theory is to be deﬁned beyond perturb ation theory , and practical problems, such as how to determine the ground states and phas es of quantum ﬁeld theories",string theory
" In string theory today we have these same kinds of problems, a nd I think there is good reason to expect that an equally powerful organizing princi ple remains to be found",string theory
" There are many reasons, as I will touch upon later, to believe that s tring theory is the correct uniﬁcation of gravity , quantum mechanics, and particle phy sics",string theory
" It is implicit, then, that the theory actually exists, and ‘exists’ does not mean just pert urbation theory ",string theory
" The nature of the organizing principle is at this point quite open, and may be very diﬀerent from what we are used to in quantum ﬁeld theory ",string theory
 One can ask whether the situation today in string theory is re ally as favorable as it was for ﬁeld theory in the early 60’s,string theory
 It is diﬃcult to know,string theory
" Then, of course, we had many more experiments to tell us how quantum ﬁeld theories actual ly behave",string theory
" T o oﬀset that, we have today more experience and greater mathematical soph istication",string theory
" As an optimist, I make an encouraging interpretation of the history , that ma ny of the key advances in ﬁeld theory—Wilson’s renormalization group, the discover y of spontaneously broken gauge symmetry as the theory of the electroweak interaction, the d iscovery of general relativity itself—were carried out largely by study of simple model sys tems and limiting behaviors, and by considerations of internal consistency ",string theory
 These same t ools are available in string theory today ,string theory
" My lectures divide into two parts—an introduction to string theory as we now under- stand it, and a look at attempts to go further",string theory
" For the introdu ction, I obviously cannot in ﬁve lectures cover the whole of superstring theory ",string theory
" Given ti me limitations, and given the broad range of interests among the students, I will try to foc us on general principles",string theory
 I will begin with conformal ﬁeld theory (2,string theory
"5 lectures), which of course has condensed mat- ter applications as well as being the central tool in string t heory ",string theory
 Section 2 (2,string theory
5 lectures) introduces string theory itself,string theory
" Section 3 (1 lecture), on d ualities and equivalences, covers 4",string theory
the steadily increasing evidence that what appear to be diﬀe rent string theories are in many cases diﬀerent ground states of a single theory ,string theory
 Section 4 (1 lecture) addresses the question of whether ‘string ﬁeld theory’ is the organizing principle we seek,string theory
" In section 5 (2 lectures) I discuss matrix models, exactly solvable string theories i n low spacetime dimensions",string theory
" I should emphasize that this is a survey of many subjects rath er than a review of any single subject (for example R-duality , on which I spend half a lecture, was the subject of a recent review [2] with nearly 300 references)",string theory
" I made an eﬀor t to choose references which will be useful to the student—a combination of reviews, some original references, and some interesting recent papers",string theory
" 1 Conformal Field Theory Much of the material in this lecture, especially the ﬁrst par t, is standard and can be found in many reviews",string theory
" The 1988 Les Houches lectures by Ginsparg [3 ] and Cardy [4] focus on conformal ﬁeld theory , the latter with emphasis on applicat ions in statistical mechanics",string theory
 Introductions to string theory with emphasis on conformal ﬁ eld theory can be found in refs,string theory
 [5]-[9],string theory
" There are a number of recent books on string th eory , though often with less emphasis on conformal techniques [10]-[14] as well as a book [15] and reprint collection [16] on conformal ﬁeld theory and statistical mechanics",string theory
 Those w ho are in no great hurry will eventually ﬁnd an expanded version of these lectures in ref,string theory
 [17],string theory
 Finally I should mention the seminal papers [18] and [19],string theory
